Newcastle disease, Cyprus
-------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 9 Jul 2013 from Dr Georgios Kyriakides, Director, Veterinary Services, Veterinary Services, Nicosia, Cyprus

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no 3
Date of start of the event: 11 Jun 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 14 Jun 2013
Report date: 9 Jul 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 9 Jul 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: October 2008
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Avian paramyxovirus 1 [APMV-1]
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (7)
[For the complete information, including dates, please go to the full report at the source URL above. The location names and "affected populations" are presented below. - Mod.AS]


Outbreak 1 (Outbreak 7): Prodromi, Paphos, Paphos
Affected population: this backyard holding consisted of 46 pet poultry, 45 laying pullets, 14 pigeons, 14 quails, 3 turkeys, 3 ducks, 1 goose, and 64 other small birds. Deaths were observed in pet poultry and laying pullets. APMV-1 was isolated on 30 Jun 2013.

Outbreak 2 (Outbreak 8): Astromeritis, Lefkosia, Lefkosia
Affected population: this backyard holding had the same boundaries as the other outbreak located in Astromeritis. APMV-1 was isolated on 3 Jul 2013.

Outbreak 3 (Outbreak 9): Mammari, Lefkosia, Lefkosia
Affected population: the 9 laying hens of this backyard holding have died in the holding. APMV-1 was isolated on 3 Jul 2013.

Outbreak 4 (Outbreak 10): Agioi Trimithias, Lefkosia, Lefkosia
Affected population: this backyard holding consisted of 67 ducks, 51 pigeons, 48 laying hens, 37 laying pullets, 29 broilers, 3 guinea fowls, and 2 quails. Deaths, clinical signs, and post-mortem lesions consistent with Newcastle disease have only been observed in chickens. APMV-1 was isolated on 5 Jul 2013.

Outbreak 5 (Outbreak 11): Geri, Lefkosia, Lefkosia
Affected population: this backyard holding consisted of 22 laying hens. APMV-1 was isolated on 5 Jul 2013.

Outbreak 6 (Outbreak 12): Prodromi, Paphos, Paphos
Affected population: this backyard holding was at a few meters distance from the other outbreak located in Prodromi and consisted of 28 laying hens. Sudden deaths and respiratory signs were observed.

Outbreak 7 (Outbreak 13): Agioi Trimithias, Lefkosia, Lefkosia
Affected population: this backyard holding consisted of 58 pet poultry, 16 turkeys, 15 guinea fowls and 1 duck. APMV-1 was isolated on 8 Jul 2013.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 7
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 589 / 133 / 103 / 486 / 0

Outbreak statistics
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 22.58 percent / 17.49 percent / 77.44 percent / 100 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: stamping out, quarantine, movement control inside the country, zoning, disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), no vaccination, no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

